# Enable CLI for Visual Studio project.

- In order to use CLI code in a VS project, you have to enable it in the settngs 
- Open you MFC (or any other c++ project) click on tools->project properties
- under the General->advanced tab look for field 
 	- 'Common Language Runtime' select: "Common Language Runtime Support (/clr)
- Apply and click OK.


create a new class using the solution tab
test writing CLI syntax. ie "System::String^ str" and intellisense should work.
